website_summaries.verdict: A good engine air filter option to choose if you don’t need the best performance but want something better than budget filters.
pros: Contains a large amount of surface area to help clean the air as it enters the engine
The thick filter will help keep out harmful debris and chemicals so the engine runs smoothly while driving
cons: Some filters contain harmful chemicals that may cause health issues

customer_reviews.title: Good Fit But the Top/Front is not Labeled
customer_reviews.text: This was a good fit for my 2004 Toyota Sienna XLE. One thing to note is that the filter is not marked as to the orientation it should go inside the air cleaner assembly. The side of the rubber gasket that has the groove on it goes down and the long edge with the notches in the groove go towards the front of the vehicle. You can't get the cover back on with it incorrectly assembled but it would be nice for them to print on it the orientation. Good quality though. Visit my blog at johnfixesstuff.blogspot.com and search for air filter to get instructions with detailed pictures on how to install this filter on your Sienna.
customer_reviews.author: John Mueller

customer_reviews.title: Does NOT fit a 2005 Toyota Sienna.
customer_reviews.text: Does not fit second gen Toyota Sienna. Old filter I had was also a Fram bought from Amazon. Went back to purchase the same item and it's different now. No Fram stamp on the filter and no arrows to direct which side is up and down. It's like a totally different flimsy filter (old Fram one was very solid and sturdy) placed inside a Fram box. Worse of all, the old Fram filter took me 30 seconds to install. This new one wouldn't go on even after 30 minutes of fiddling. This product obviously does NOT fit a 2005 Toyota Sienna. Amazon and Fram owes me 30 minutes of my time back!
customer_reviews.author: Orin

customer_reviews.title: some of the hose receptors become brittle and can break very easy. You will then have to improvise if they ...
customer_reviews.text: Fits my vehicle perfectly.....2007 Sienna 3.5. NOTE: Be very careful removing cover of air filter. Remove as many hoses as possible. Due to age, some of the hose receptors become brittle and can break very easy. You will then have to improvise if they crack and break. When removing hoses, do so with as little pressure as possible. You might want to cut the hose off and just scrape sway what is left on the receptor as there is enough hose left to reattach. Don't force anything.

customer_reviews.text: It's a little too long. You can't close the cover. I did try turning it around as the old one I have was marked front. UPDATE: Thanks to another reviewer who did in fact put this into a 2009 Lexus RX350 I just tried again and it does indeed fit.
